        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-04-08 15:54:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nCompile error is on el7: percpu_counter_init has 3 parameters instead of 2. It's going to take me awhile to figure out how to fix/test for that kernel.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8011b7f7d50abf3e511a3d44594831d68bf2f357",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-04-08 16:04:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI see that some code already has:\n\n #ifdef HAVE_PERCPU_COUNTER_INIT_GFP_FLAG\n        return percpu_counter_init(&ldlm_granted_total, 0, GFP_KERNEL);\n #else\n        return percpu_counter_init(&ldlm_granted_total, 0);\n #endif",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "aaee6c7881db620ec38fdaee89d8019da24a07f1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-04-08 16:05:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThough it may be that you should use \"GFP_NOFS\" instead of GFP_KERNEL.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c2b358c4de43692f8a66dce2f3406f0a5e1792c2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-04-08 16:18:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAt a high level, it would be better to take a look at lprocfs_counter_*() to move that infrastructure over to use the kernel percpu_*() infrastructure internally, instead of the home-grown mechanism that is used today.  This would optimize all of the lprocfs_counter_*() users instead of just this one stat.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d2abc57f6dd2bc96ee92ba38e8231dca3b435844",
      "author": {
